1
00:00:29,990 --> 00:00:33,199
Over not making
loan payments on time?

2
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,440
Nothing to worry about?

3
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:37,700
It's all right. I'll sort it out.

4
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:39,480
Save, I like you.

5
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:44,880
Alright, from now on,
we're growing our own vegetables.

6
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:49,060
You'll take turns watering them.
Deal?

7
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:50,239
- Deal.
- Deal.

8
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,600
Louder.

9
00:00:51,630 --> 00:00:54,000
- Deal.
- Deal.

10
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:58,480
Hurry up.

11
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,230
Hurry, Mabel. Come on.

12
00:01:03,310 --> 00:01:04,240
Just open it.
Let's start.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,680
Hey Snow, hold on.
I'm still reading that page.

14
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,800
You're such a slow reader.

15
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,720
Done?

16
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,120
Okay, next page.

17
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:30,560
What are you doing here?

18
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,840
Oh, my dear.

19
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:56,720
- Grandpa.
- Grandpa.

20
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,120
You've gone too far.

21
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:08,440
Cute, isn't it?

22
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:13,280
Run, run.

23
00:02:13,490 --> 00:02:14,490
Hey.

24
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,660
Kids.

25
00:02:37,730 --> 00:02:38,730
Shh.

26
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:40,960
Don't tell anyone.

27
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:02,360
"Until the Time is Right."

28
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:04,440
Uhm.

29
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,400
Must I write this kind of thing?

30
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,360
Mmm.

31
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,880
A big shock right from page one.

32
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:34,160
Gets worse in the middle. Hmm.

33
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:00,510
Save, I like you.

34
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,600
Like me?

35
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,920
Yeah.

36
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,680
I like you too.

37
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:11,560
Why else have we been friends
since seventh grade?

38
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,320
No.

39
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,450
Not as a friend.

40
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:19,680
What do you mean?
Are you losing it?

41
00:04:22,110 --> 00:04:23,440
I like you, Save.

42
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,400
More than a friend.

43
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,640
Be serious.

44
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,640
You messing with me?

45
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,200
I'm not.

46
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:38,920
Are you... rejecting me?

47
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,480
No.

48
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:46,600
I just don't know what I did
to make you feel that way.

49
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:50,680
I don't know.
I just like being around you.

50
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:54,000
And I started feeling like
I wanted to be with you.

51
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,200
At first, I wasn't sure.

52
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,300
Thought I was losing it,
like you said.

53
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,560
But now, I'm sure.

54
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,850
You're more than a friend to me.

55
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,680
But to me, you're not.

56
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,920
Huh.

57
00:05:11,921 --> 00:05:13,120
I kind of figured.

58
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,600
So why bring it up?

59
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,200
Because I've been hiding it
for too long.

60
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,119
I'm sorry.

61
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,320
Don't be.

62
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:33,710
Save.

63
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:36,240
Can I ask you something?

64
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:42,080
Can you just...
forget what I said?

65
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:46,360
Pretend I never said it.

66
00:05:47,650 --> 00:05:48,720
Can you do that?

67
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:54,200
I still want to be your friend.

68
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:58,600
How's that supposed to work?

69
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:09,400
"Guy: Home yet? I'm already home."

70
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,260
"Why not reading my texts?"

71
00:06:12,050 --> 00:06:12,980
"Taking a dump?"

72
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,320
"Hahaha."

73
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:22,210
"The broad frame growls
with a fierce rumble"

74
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,480
"like a crack of thunder."

75
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:29,919
"Burning lips press
along every tender spot"

76
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:32,040
"of the slender form in his arms"

77
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:37,040
"before sliding up
to meet the ice-cold lips."

78
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:41,559
"Tongue slipping in
to taste the sweetness within."

79
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:44,960
"As the slender form cries out
as if drawing a final breath"

80
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:49,759
"the young alpha bends down
and bites the omega's neck"

81
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:53,800
"to bind the two of them
together, forever."

82
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,640
Whew.

83
00:06:57,120 --> 00:07:01,040
The most incredible scene of passion
I've ever read.

84
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,840
Father, it's Mart.

85
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:08,990
Come in.

86
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:13,320
Father, we have a problem.

87
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:17,000
Something bad has happened.

88
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,320
What happened?

89
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:21,960
Media rot is dragging our society
into the gutter.

90
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:25,480
No wonder kids are going
off the rails everywhere.

91
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:29,640
Calm down.
Tell me again, what happened?

92
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:34,520
The kids were reading a BL novel.
Explicit stuff.

93
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,400
What?

94
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,000
Where did they get it?

95
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,400
From a friend at school.

96
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,960
Return it. No more reading it.

97
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,519
But why, Grandpa?

98
00:07:57,520 --> 00:08:00,440
Everyone reads BL novels these days.

99
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:03,010
That's right. The world's opened up.

100
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:06,160
People need their daily
BL fix now, Director.

101
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:08,720
Daily BL fix.
What does that even mean?

102
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:12,959
BL fix means consuming gay content.

103
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,439
Because it's adorable.

104
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:16,080
- Adorable.
- Adorable.

105
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:17,520
Uhm-hmm...

106
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,550
You certainly have
a way with words.

107
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,839
There are actually
a lot more, Grandpa.

108
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:26,090
We can teach you if you want.

109
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:29,360
That's enough.
This is getting out of hand.

110
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,190
I said do not read it.

111
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:33,600
The content is simply inappropriate.

112
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,300
How, Grandpa?

113
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:39,000
Are you against LGBTQ people?

114
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,560
I'm not against that.

115
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:44,360
And I don't think it's wrong.

116
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:47,200
What's wrong is its 18+ material.

117
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,640
Are any of you that old yet?

118
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,240
Age is just a number.

119
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:53,840
That's enough.

120
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,520
As far as I'm concerned,
you're still children.

121
00:08:57,980 --> 00:09:00,159
You don't yet have
the judgment to know

122
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,760
what's appropriate and what isn't.

123
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,480
So don't let me catch you

124
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,160
sneaking off to read it again.

125
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,120
Understood?

126
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,720
- Yes.
- Yes.

127
00:09:50,110 --> 00:09:51,110
Wait.

128
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,840
Am I reading this right?

129
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,320
Men can get pregnant?

130
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:58,520
That's shocking.

131
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:06,920
Father, it's me. Here to clean.

132
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,240
Ah... come in.

133
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,600
Dad.

134
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Hehe.

135
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,920
You could've knocked.

136
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:01,280
Sorry, Dad.

137
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:05,080
The tap's broken. I need some cash
to buy a new one.

138
00:11:05,410 --> 00:11:06,720
Again?

139
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,840
It's necessary, Dad.

140
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,280
Unless you want to
just leave it broken.

141
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:14,720
Hold on. Maybe it can be fixed.

142
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:15,870
Hmm?

143
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:18,040
- Um.
- Let's go.

144
00:11:18,070 --> 00:11:19,350
Probably not, Dad.

145
00:11:19,370 --> 00:11:20,770
We'll need a new one.

146
00:11:20,970 --> 00:11:22,480
You never even try to fix things.

147
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,480
Go, go.

148
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,800
Save, pass it over.

149
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,880
Pass the ball. Come on.

150
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:37,560
Save.

151
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,230
Why didn't you pass to me?

152
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:46,680
I zoned out for a second.

153
00:11:54,450 --> 00:11:55,640
Is that a braised egg?

154
00:11:56,430 --> 00:11:59,060
I got no egg.
And we paid the same price.

155
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:01,030
- Oh-ho.
- What is this?

156
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:02,270
Here, take mine.

157
00:12:03,130 --> 00:12:04,440
Hey, scoot over.

158
00:12:04,570 --> 00:12:06,130
What? There are plenty of seats.

159
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,160
Oh, Save.

160
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,790
Pheem, going to Siam tonight?

161
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,160
Yeah.

162
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:14,200
I want to try
that place you showed me.

163
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,480
Oh, right. Yeah, sure.

164
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:17,880
Hey, I'm coming too.

165
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,510
Up to you.

166
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,480
What about me?

167
00:12:20,481 --> 00:12:22,240
- You guys don't want me?
- Up to you.

168
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:23,450
Hey, what's the deal?

169
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:24,440
Just come with us.

170
00:12:24,470 --> 00:12:26,280
I don't want you talking
behind my back.

171
00:12:28,170 --> 00:12:31,120
I know you, always buying new parts.

172
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:33,550
If it can be fixed,
you should learn how to.

173
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:36,600
Oh, who could ever
match your skills?

174
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:40,550
That sounds a little sarcastic.

175
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:43,150
No. I genuinely mean it.

176
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,280
Think you can fix that now?

177
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,120
Yes, sir.

178
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:48,750
Good.

179
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:55,239
Oh, a delivery.
I'd better get back to work.

180
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,760
Carry on.

181
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,599
- Oui.
- Yes.

182
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,960
Were you in my room just now?

183
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,240
No, Director. What's wrong?

184
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:39,920
I can't find something.

185
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:43,370
You should ask Mart, Director.
I saw her go in to clean.

186
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,680
Not heading out?

187
00:14:52,950 --> 00:14:54,540
It was canceled.

188
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,560
But what are you doing here?

189
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:57,920
Well...

190
00:14:58,310 --> 00:15:00,120
looking for that thing
you borrowed from me.

191
00:15:00,410 --> 00:15:01,450
- Borrowed.
- Hmm.

192
00:15:02,070 --> 00:15:03,320
What did I borrow from you?

193
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,440
That thing.

194
00:15:04,441 --> 00:15:05,759
Which thing?

195
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:08,400
That thing.
How do you forget so fast?

196
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,600
The whole house is
losing their minds.

197
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:14,290
Forget it. I'm done talking.
If you find it, just return it.

198
00:15:14,430 --> 00:15:15,430
Hmm?

199
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:17,580
Uh.

200
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:22,080
What did I borrow from him?

201
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,000
Father, I found this in your office.

202
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:47,280
Did the kids get another book?

203
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,040
- Huh.
- Well...

204
00:15:49,110 --> 00:15:52,920
Nice disguise.
They thought we wouldn't catch on.

205
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:56,920
We can't let this slide.
A real punishment this time.

206
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,770
It's not necessary.

207
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:00,790
I'll talk to them.

208
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:03,080
Father, please don't.

209
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:06,640
If we're lenient, there's no telling
what they'll pull next.

210
00:16:06,930 --> 00:16:08,759
We have to nip this in the bud.

211
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:12,759
Calm down. It's not
that big of a deal.

212
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:15,320
Ah... it is, Father.

213
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:19,480
Let it slide once,
and they won't stop there.

214
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,000
It's okay. Give that to me.

215
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,560
Is this a good idea?

216
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,120
It is.

217
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,660
I don't think it is.

218
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:37,310
- Trust me.
- Father.

219
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:38,930
Please don't.

220
00:16:39,810 --> 00:16:40,810
Please.

221
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,120
Let me keep this.

222
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:48,200
This time I'll talk to them.

223
00:16:54,970 --> 00:16:56,040
Whose book is this?

224
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:00,999
Admit it.

225
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,160
It's not mine, Mom.

226
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,600
- Not mine either.
- Not mine.

227
00:17:05,210 --> 00:17:06,800
So that's how you're gonna play.

228
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:09,359
Ow... it isn't ours, Mom.

229
00:17:09,360 --> 00:17:10,519
What's there to admit?

230
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:13,919
You're lying.
If it's not yours, then whose is it?

231
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:16,679
Who in this house
reads this kind of novel

232
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,680
besides you kids?

233
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:19,840
Own up.

234
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,810
Well... ahem. Mart.

235
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:25,160
Just let it go.

236
00:17:25,780 --> 00:17:28,600
I cannot. This is serious.

237
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,000
They'll all go down the wrong path.

238
00:17:31,070 --> 00:17:34,360
What wrong path?
It's just about two men in love.

239
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,960
It's full of dirty scenes.

240
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,760
And you're still kids.

241
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,800
So nobody's going to admit it?

242
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:45,000
It really isn't ours.

243
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:46,160
That's right.

244
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:48,840
Fine. In that case,

245
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:51,010
no dinner tonight.

246
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,010
- What?
- What?

247
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:54,679
Auntie Mart, it's not ours. Honest.

248
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:56,560
- That's not fair.
- Mom, come on.

249
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:57,330
Mart. Mart.
Ahem.

250
00:17:58,170 --> 00:17:59,060
Come here.

251
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,600
What is it, Father?

252
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:01,960
Just come here.

253
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,480
What is this?

254
00:18:05,620 --> 00:18:08,599
- Oh come on.
- That's so unfair, Auntie Mart.

255
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:09,600
Hold on.

256
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,620
If it's not ours,

257
00:18:12,570 --> 00:18:13,800
then who does it belong to?

258
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,120
Yeah, whose book?

259
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:29,960
- Father.
- Hmm.

260
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:32,360
Please don't make this
harder for me.

261
00:18:32,430 --> 00:18:33,870
I have to punish them.

262
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:37,560
That's enough. Leave them alone.

263
00:18:38,270 --> 00:18:40,360
But they broke the rules.

264
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,000
Let it go this once.

265
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,520
What is going on?
This isn't like you at all.

266
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:48,760
It doesn't matter.
They are getting punished.

267
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,280
Mart. Mart.

268
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,560
That book is mine.

269
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,160
I'm sorry.

270
00:18:55,190 --> 00:18:57,580
This book. It belongs to me.

271
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,360
Leave the kids out of it.

272
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:03,319
You don't have to go this far
to protect them.

273
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:05,840
I'm not protecting anyone.
It's really mine.

274
00:19:06,060 --> 00:19:09,319
Uh... but how could it be yours?

275
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:11,590
Since when did you
even glance at this?

276
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:16,770
Well... I'm planning
to write a BL novel

277
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,420
to pay off the debt.

278
00:19:22,530 --> 00:19:24,650
BL novel? What is it?

279
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:28,679
Come on.
It's boys' love romance novel.

280
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:31,680
You can't write that, Dad.
That's not you.

281
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,440
I can. I just need some practice.

282
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:39,120
Dad, a great writer like you,
taking on this genre?

283
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:41,600
People are really
into it these days.

284
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:44,640
And if it sells,
the money's decent.

285
00:19:45,170 --> 00:19:46,170
Please don't, Dad.

286
00:19:47,130 --> 00:19:48,399
There has to be a better way.

287
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:51,800
You haven't written a novel
in over thirty years.

288
00:19:52,770 --> 00:19:55,160
You think you can just
pick it back up now?

289
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,160
I said I can, didn't I?

290
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,360
Just sell the place, Dad.

291
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:07,340
Sun, how did you know about this?

292
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,120
I told him.

293
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,040
Why did you?

294
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:14,320
He is his son and your kid brother.

295
00:20:14,710 --> 00:20:16,720
He's family.

296
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:19,160
He has every right
to know what's going on.

297
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,919
Dad, if you really can't hold on,

298
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:29,000
I think...
you'd better sell the orphanage.

299
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:31,220
It'll relieve you of this stress.

300
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,880
I'm not selling.

301
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,880
Then you'll need to open up
for more donations.

302
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:39,679
Or reach out to former residents
with the means to help.

303
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:41,040
Anything that can cover the debt.

304
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,079
That could work.

305
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:46,800
We've never once told them
that we're struggling.

306
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:51,080
If we put the word out,
I'm sure they would want to help.

307
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,400
No.

308
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:56,600
They have their own lives now.

309
00:20:56,910 --> 00:21:00,800
I've raised these kids
hoping to see them thrive.

310
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:02,840
Not to have them repay anything.

311
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,730
Grandmother, please sit down.

312
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,720
Come, come. Right there.

313
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:12,680
Dad, we can't just keep
going like this.

314
00:21:13,370 --> 00:21:14,680
You must do something.

315
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:17,480
I'm working on it.

316
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,880
The bank won't wait for that.

317
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:21,630
Sun, don't push him like that.

318
00:21:21,670 --> 00:21:23,400
I'm just laying out the facts.

319
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,520
Dad, I don't see any other way.

320
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:32,040
The best option now is to sell.
Plain and simple.

321
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:33,480
No.

322
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,479
Selling is not an option.

323
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,920
Why not?

324
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,040
You may eat.

325
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,000
All right. Enjoy.

326
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,040
Luang (honorific), sir.

327
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:58,680
What is it, Phi Boonma?

328
00:22:00,350 --> 00:22:02,680
Could I trouble you
to keep an eye on Tone?

329
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,320
Just through the afternoon.

330
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,760
I'll pick him up
when I'm done with work.

331
00:22:06,790 --> 00:22:08,110
My wife just passed.

332
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:10,320
There's no one to look after him.

333
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,840
Of course. I'll take care of him.

334
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,920
Thank you, Luang.

335
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:17,720
All right, Tone. Greet him properly.

336
00:22:18,050 --> 00:22:19,050
Hmm.

337
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:22,200
Come, just in time for a meal.

338
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:26,319
Luang, the villagers
raised this sum.

339
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,520
Please keep it.

340
00:22:30,630 --> 00:22:31,640
It's a lot of money.

341
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,960
I can't.

342
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,199
Please take it.

343
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:39,080
We understand your dedication
to care for these children.

344
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:40,960
We all want to do our part.

345
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:44,200
You could purchase
the adjoining land

346
00:22:44,260 --> 00:22:46,610
and build a proper house for them.

347
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:50,520
So they don't have to
put up with cramped living.

348
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,970
Please accept it, Luang (honorific).

349
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:59,640
I don't know how to...
thank you on behalf of the children.

350
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:03,080
We're happy to support
your dedication.

351
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:07,320
I promise I will use this land

352
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:10,400
for the good of these children.
Always.

353
00:23:11,110 --> 00:23:13,120
The land isn't ours to sell

354
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:16,719
because the villagers
donated their money

355
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,520
to find a home for children in need.

356
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:21,600
Selling it
would betray that purpose.

357
00:23:21,980 --> 00:23:22,920
It's not for sale.

358
00:23:22,921 --> 00:23:24,480
But that was so long ago, Dad.

359
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:26,559
The donors are all gone now.

360
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:28,000
I'm still here.

361
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,880
I will never compromise
my grandfather's vision.

362
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:40,120
Honestly, I don't agree
with selling it either.

363
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:41,840
Stay out of this, Sun.

364
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:44,320
We'll find our own way.

365
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,960
Then I have nothing more to say.

366
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:52,760
Thank you for coming.

367
00:23:53,570 --> 00:23:56,000
I'll head out then. Back to work.

368
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,680
Bye, Dad.

369
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:13,480
That's Sun for you.

370
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:23,260
Nevertheless, keep this
from Save and Snow.

371
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,640
They'll only worry.

372
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:35,169
Don't get there. Come on, quick.

373
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:37,080
Save. Hey, Save.

374
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,020
Pass it over.

375
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:40,920
Save, pass. Come on.

376
00:24:44,550 --> 00:24:45,350
Ow.

377
00:24:45,380 --> 00:24:46,640
- Oh, come on.
- Aw.

378
00:24:46,940 --> 00:24:48,440
- What?
- Hate the game, guys.

379
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:48,990
Sorry.

380
00:24:49,010 --> 00:24:50,680
- Unbelievable.
- Let's go. Go.

381
00:24:50,710 --> 00:24:51,710
Try harder.

382
00:24:52,610 --> 00:24:54,000
Nice. Jang, that was nice.

383
00:25:00,570 --> 00:25:03,320
- Heh.
- Enough.

384
00:25:04,850 --> 00:25:06,120
Dude, it wasn't my fault.

385
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:07,820
Hey.

386
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,100
- Ron.
- Oh, hey.

387
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,140
- Hey.
- Hey.

388
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:14,359
Ron, you gaming tonight?

389
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,880
Sure, nine o'clock, yeah?

390
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,390
- Don't go dark on us again.
- He will.

391
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,000
All the time, this guy.

392
00:25:20,430 --> 00:25:21,400
Never.

393
00:25:21,401 --> 00:25:22,840
- Never what?
- Never?

394
00:25:23,010 --> 00:25:25,280
- Haha.
- Haha.

395
00:25:26,260 --> 00:25:28,280
So stuffed, man.

396
00:25:28,540 --> 00:25:29,540
Yeah, up to here.

397
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,400
Can't do soccer now. Too full.

398
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:33,160
- So full.
- Still full.

399
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:35,720
Ugh.

400
00:25:36,170 --> 00:25:39,119
- Hey, Jang, Pheem, free tickets.
- You got them?

401
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,520
- Hold on.
- Free to what?

402
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:41,600
Go ask him.

403
00:25:42,930 --> 00:25:43,970
We need to talk.

404
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:46,599
I want to go to class.

405
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:47,920
Class? You?

406
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,640
Yeah.

407
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:52,640
Just talk to me.

408
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:55,680
Come on.

409
00:25:57,870 --> 00:25:58,910
What's wrong with you?

410
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,520
Nothing.

411
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,000
You're not yourself.

412
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:03,920
I am myself.

413
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:05,800
You said you wouldn't act weird.

414
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:11,120
You think it's that easy?

415
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,070
Us the way we were?

416
00:26:13,890 --> 00:26:15,640
After you told me you liked me?

417
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:17,860
You hate me now?

418
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:19,220
No.

419
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:21,920
I make you feel uncomfortable?

420
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:23,300
Huh.

421
00:26:26,790 --> 00:26:28,480
Fine. I'm sorry.

422
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,680
I told you, stop apologizing.

423
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:32,040
This is on me.

424
00:26:32,650 --> 00:26:34,080
I ruined everything.

425
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:37,040
From now on, I won't be around you.

426
00:26:58,810 --> 00:26:59,880
Whew.

427
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,360
"1"

428
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:20,760
Oh, hi.

429
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:23,960
Hey, Save. Humor me this.

430
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,960
What's it like
when a boy likes another boy?

431
00:28:27,610 --> 00:28:28,620
What kind of question is that?

432
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:31,119
Well, I'm writing a BL novel.

433
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:33,120
- Ha? A BL novel?
- Yeah.

434
00:28:33,610 --> 00:28:34,960
You got nothing else?

435
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:38,240
I just want to try.
Help me out a little.

436
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:42,119
Tell me how it feels
when two boys like each other.

437
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,200
Oy, you got the wrong boy.
How should I know?

438
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:46,629
I'm not into boys.

439
00:28:46,630 --> 00:28:48,960
Ow, you're a teenager.

440
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:52,559
Some of your friends
may be like that. Right?

441
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:54,720
None. Just don't write it, Grandpa.

442
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,240
Drop it. Quit.

443
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,520
You can't pull off a BL novel.

444
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:01,410
Huh.

445
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:03,680
Why got mad?

446
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:14,210
Okay.

447
00:29:17,450 --> 00:29:19,200
Yeah, good.

448
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:24,080
Mart, I don't think
Dad can write that novel.

449
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:26,200
Hmm. That's what I figured.

450
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:29,680
So what do we do then?

451
00:29:30,660 --> 00:29:31,660
Hmm.

452
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,640
We could try selling something.

453
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:37,180
Who's got money in this economy?

454
00:29:37,230 --> 00:29:38,400
Well.

455
00:29:39,430 --> 00:29:42,520
We gotta come up with
things they want to buy.

456
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:44,200
Like what?

457
00:29:44,230 --> 00:29:46,240
Help me think.

458
00:29:46,290 --> 00:29:47,800
I'm helping and thinking.

459
00:29:50,340 --> 00:29:53,580
Even if we figure it out,
who knows if we can make them?

460
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:55,360
That's the question.

461
00:29:56,770 --> 00:29:58,600
Oh, Grandmother.

462
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:01,280
Oh, stop, stop.

463
00:30:01,780 --> 00:30:04,240
Hmm. You're at it again.

464
00:30:07,190 --> 00:30:09,280
Sanae Chan, The Royal Recipe.

465
00:30:13,530 --> 00:30:14,999
Phi Sorn. Phi Sorn.

466
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,520
Yeah? What is it?

467
00:30:17,150 --> 00:30:20,920
Hmph. Are you deaf?
Didn't you hear me?

468
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:25,440
Grandmother, thank you.

469
00:30:25,540 --> 00:30:29,760
You really came through for us.
Thank you.

470
00:30:36,380 --> 00:30:37,380
What?

471
00:30:39,410 --> 00:30:42,080
Oh, now it just clicks.

472
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,079
Dad used to tell me

473
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,229
that when Grandmother was young,

474
00:30:47,230 --> 00:30:49,920
she studied confectionery
at the palace.

475
00:30:50,330 --> 00:30:54,400
These recipes are
over a hundred years old.

476
00:30:58,780 --> 00:30:59,780
Ah-ha.

477
00:31:01,550 --> 00:31:02,680
Now sift.

478
00:31:08,130 --> 00:31:08,920
All right.

479
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:10,160
Oh, hmph.

480
00:31:12,190 --> 00:31:15,140
Oh, no. Like this.

481
00:31:15,260 --> 00:31:17,520
Just tap.

482
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:19,240
- I see.
- Be patient.

483
00:31:19,260 --> 00:31:21,679
Or it'll be all over the place.

484
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:22,770
- Got it.
- Yeah.

485
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:25,990
Okay.

486
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:40,840
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

487
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:44,110
Okay. Put this in.

488
00:31:44,150 --> 00:31:45,150
100 grams.

489
00:31:47,430 --> 00:31:48,430
Hold on.

490
00:31:58,860 --> 00:32:00,800
And this.

491
00:32:05,730 --> 00:32:09,080
Now... mix well.

492
00:32:26,550 --> 00:32:29,120
- Phi Sorn, nice color, see?
- Oh, wow.

493
00:32:31,010 --> 00:32:32,560
- It's coming together.
- Yes, yes.

494
00:32:32,590 --> 00:32:33,600
Get the tray.

495
00:32:33,620 --> 00:32:34,620
Here.

496
00:32:36,650 --> 00:32:38,080
Okay. Ready.

497
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:46,920
Twenty-three.

498
00:32:50,190 --> 00:32:51,320
That's ten.

499
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:03,780
Here. Here.

500
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:06,320
- Nice, huh?
- Here...

501
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:12,559
Oh, forgive its shape for now.

502
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:14,360
Let's get the flavor right first.

503
00:33:28,430 --> 00:33:29,840
Oh, no. Grandmother.

504
00:33:30,610 --> 00:33:31,610
Huh.

505
00:33:32,050 --> 00:33:35,660
Um. Didn't we get the right flavor?

506
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:39,280
I guess it's really bad
that she spits it out.

507
00:33:39,410 --> 00:33:40,530
Oh, Phi Sorn.

508
00:33:40,610 --> 00:33:42,760
I did say it tasted strange.

509
00:33:45,610 --> 00:33:47,640
I will try again, Grandmother.

510
00:34:14,930 --> 00:34:16,360
Hey, Guy.

511
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:18,130
- Guy.
- Oh.

512
00:34:27,030 --> 00:34:28,370
Didn't he see me?

513
00:34:28,390 --> 00:34:30,299
He saw me, yeah?
He looked right at me.

514
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:31,640
- He did.
- Yeah, man.

515
00:34:51,610 --> 00:34:52,720
Uh... oops.

516
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:57,600
Phi Sorn, what a mess.

517
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:58,280
Um...

518
00:34:58,281 --> 00:35:00,970
- Phi Sorn.
- It happens. No big deal.

519
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:03,200
- Be careful.
- I'll just try again.

520
00:35:03,220 --> 00:35:06,280
- It's a big bowl there.
- I don't want to break the yolk.

521
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,080
Ugh.

522
00:35:07,081 --> 00:35:08,320
- I'm trying, okay?
- Oh?

523
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:13,180
We haven't made any money yet.

524
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:14,880
- But eggs are out.
- Mom, Dad.

525
00:35:14,910 --> 00:35:16,739
What is all this mess?

526
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:19,080
Your mom wants to
make sweets to sell.

527
00:35:19,190 --> 00:35:21,399
What? Selling sweets?

528
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,520
That's food, right?

529
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:26,560
Aw... a little encouragement
would be nice.

530
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,280
I hope nobody gets food poisoning.

531
00:35:29,570 --> 00:35:32,999
You. Wipe that off.

532
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:35,360
- There you go.
- Oh, Dad.

533
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:56,710
Here. Check this out.
Hehe.

534
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,480
Ugh.

535
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:24,920
Hmm.

536
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,360
Huh.

537
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:18,880
Hmm?

538
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:26,720
Is it good now?

539
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,520
- Heh.
- Ha!

540
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:35,200
We did it, Phi Sorn. We got it.

541
00:38:35,230 --> 00:38:36,230
Eh-haha.

542
00:38:40,010 --> 00:38:41,920
I did great.

543
00:38:50,500 --> 00:38:51,500
Careful.

544
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:54,920
- Oh, wow.
- Wow.

545
00:38:57,950 --> 00:38:59,510
Go ahead. Try some.

546
00:39:00,210 --> 00:39:01,279
- Yes.
- Yeah.

547
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:02,530
Slow down. Slow down.

548
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:05,260
No need to fight over them.
They're all good.

549
00:39:08,570 --> 00:39:11,000
Heck. Heck.

550
00:39:11,900 --> 00:39:14,200
Heck. Heck.

551
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:17,000
Mom, what did you give us?

552
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,680
Dirt mixed with sugar?

553
00:39:19,450 --> 00:39:20,450
Ow.

554
00:39:21,660 --> 00:39:23,340
A sweet is supposed to be sweet.

555
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:25,440
If it's bland,
can you call it a sweet?

556
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:27,360
Let's go find some water.

557
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,320
Hmph.

558
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,440
Is it that bad?

559
00:39:35,810 --> 00:39:36,810
Mm-hmm.

560
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:39,160
The kids just don't
have the palate.

561
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:42,920
Royal palace confectionery
isn't for everyone.

562
00:39:43,950 --> 00:39:44,950
Hmph.

563
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,880
Really.

564
00:39:50,780 --> 00:39:52,240
Have a taste, Khun (honorific) On.

565
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,120
Hmm.

566
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:10,200
Throat-burning sweet, Khun Mart.

567
00:40:10,860 --> 00:40:11,860
Really?

568
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,320
It is.

569
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:18,040
I can't get it down.

570
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:29,240
Water...

571
00:40:30,290 --> 00:40:32,040
Here, water. Water.

572
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:43,809
Can I be honest with you?

573
00:40:43,810 --> 00:40:46,919
Yes, please. I need the feedback.

574
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:49,400
It's very rough going down,
Khun Mart.

575
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:52,040
It's sticky. Can't swallow it.

576
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:55,560
I'm sorry. I really can't take it.

577
00:41:10,220 --> 00:41:11,360
Have some water.

578
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,480
So how is it?

579
00:41:15,510 --> 00:41:18,240
Hmm. I think the recipe needs
a bit of tweaking.

580
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,520
Yeah...

581
00:41:20,710 --> 00:41:23,510
You used to make sweets, Khun Phon.
Could you advise me?

582
00:41:23,670 --> 00:41:24,670
Of course.

583
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:28,640
Hmm... have you ever tried
Japanese sweets?

584
00:41:28,830 --> 00:41:30,359
The texture is much smoother.

585
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,239
And the sweetness isn't as sharp.

586
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:35,400
You can apply that to your recipe.

587
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:38,400
Really? How would I go about that?

588
00:42:11,170 --> 00:42:12,690
Is something the matter, Grandpa?

589
00:42:13,700 --> 00:42:16,680
Snow, will you read this?

590
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:18,360
What is it?

591
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:20,720
BL novel.

592
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:23,000
Ump...

593
00:42:23,560 --> 00:42:24,880
You wrote this?

594
00:42:25,550 --> 00:42:26,550
Mm-hmm.

595
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:30,320
Awesome. That's my grandpa.

596
00:42:30,350 --> 00:42:31,350
Good.

597
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:01,520
"Hew"? What does it mean?

598
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,919
That word is pronounced "wae."

599
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,640
Hor-wor-ae, Wae.

600
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:08,519
What does it mean?

601
00:43:08,520 --> 00:43:10,550
Your nagging tone
when you chew someone out.

602
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:13,800
Have they never
covered this in school?

603
00:43:15,320 --> 00:43:18,439
No... never heard it before.

604
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:19,760
Is it even Thai?

605
00:43:25,580 --> 00:43:28,760
See... that makes it fun.

606
00:43:48,570 --> 00:43:49,570
You find it fun?

607
00:43:52,080 --> 00:43:53,080
Hmm...

608
00:43:54,390 --> 00:43:56,280
You wanna get AI to help?

609
00:43:57,400 --> 00:43:58,400
Let who help?

610
00:43:58,800 --> 00:43:59,800
AI.

611
00:44:00,130 --> 00:44:01,800
It's an app on the phone.

612
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:04,760
Can I borrow your phone?

613
00:44:12,300 --> 00:44:13,540
Thank you.

614
00:44:27,570 --> 00:44:28,680
Hello.

615
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:33,430
"Hello. How can I help you today?"

616
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:40,280
Help me write a fun BL novel.

617
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,200
"What novel did you say?"

618
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:48,440
A gay novel.

619
00:44:51,380 --> 00:44:53,519
"I'm sorry. You like gay content?"

620
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:54,960
Huh... no!

621
00:44:55,590 --> 00:44:57,920
No. You don't understand me.

622
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,520
Good. Serves you right.

623
00:45:09,860 --> 00:45:11,600
Ta-da.

624
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:16,360
Mabel and Yoyo are here
to give feedback today.

625
00:45:18,950 --> 00:45:19,950
Mm-hmm.

626
00:45:36,620 --> 00:45:39,760
This paragraph reads a lot like
"Sick Crush on My Senior."

627
00:45:41,440 --> 00:45:44,120
That part is just like
"Phi Nuea, My Undoing."

628
00:45:46,510 --> 00:45:48,560
Did you yoink from other novels?

629
00:45:49,150 --> 00:45:50,270
What does yoink mean?

630
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:53,000
You lifted it
from someone else's work.

631
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:55,820
I didn't lift anything.
It's just that...

632
00:45:56,960 --> 00:45:58,280
I had AI help me.

633
00:46:00,730 --> 00:46:02,410
That's not okay, Grandpa.

634
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:05,200
Hmm?

635
00:46:15,220 --> 00:46:19,820
"Guy: Home yet? Not reading
my texts? Taking a dump?"

636
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:23,510
"Save: Hey..."

637
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:34,600
Save.

638
00:46:35,100 --> 00:46:36,100
Yeah?

639
00:46:36,990 --> 00:46:38,380
Oh, whew.

640
00:46:39,590 --> 00:46:41,350
Getting ready to be fried?

641
00:46:42,130 --> 00:46:43,130
Not funny.

642
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:45,639
Fetch me field trip permission slips
from Grandpa's room

643
00:46:45,640 --> 00:46:46,920
and hand them out to the kids.

644
00:46:48,770 --> 00:46:49,770
Sure.

645
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:44,360
"Demand for Repayment
and Notice of Legal Action."

646
00:47:49,250 --> 00:47:51,310
"Balance: 530 baht."

647
00:48:17,670 --> 00:48:20,560
Told you it wouldn't work.

648
00:48:21,190 --> 00:48:24,900
You complain a lot,
and it doesn't help anything.

649
00:48:25,200 --> 00:48:29,560
It's the truth.
This kind of sweet is out of style.

650
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,120
All that money down the drain.

651
00:48:32,560 --> 00:48:34,239
At least we tried

652
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:36,880
to save the house
from getting repossessed.

653
00:48:38,220 --> 00:48:40,399
This place is home to these kids.

654
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:42,840
A lot of them
have nowhere else to go.

655
00:48:42,900 --> 00:48:44,760
We're the only family they have.

656
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:45,560
Phi Save, play with us.

657
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:48,920
Yeah, I'll be right there.

658
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:50,360
Hurry up.

659
00:49:51,240 --> 00:49:52,240
Mm-hmm.

660
00:49:55,220 --> 00:49:57,080
- Ball.
- Yeah, catch.

661
00:50:01,560 --> 00:50:04,920
How are you, Jingjai?
Wanna play with your friends?

662
00:50:05,050 --> 00:50:07,120
Come. I will take you.

663
00:50:08,420 --> 00:50:10,440
That's it, sweetheart.

664
00:50:10,710 --> 00:50:12,800
Your friends are drawing something.

665
00:50:50,280 --> 00:50:51,280
Grandpa...

666
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:53,840
How's the novel coming along?

667
00:50:54,920 --> 00:50:57,720
Snow read it. Not feeling it.

668
00:50:58,750 --> 00:51:00,720
The boy-boy energy just isn't there.

669
00:51:01,280 --> 00:51:05,440
Beats me. I've never once
been in love with a man.

670
00:51:06,620 --> 00:51:10,360
And none of my friends
have ever been that way either.

671
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:19,000
Grandpa.

672
00:51:19,420 --> 00:51:22,870
You think your BL novel
will pay off our debt?

673
00:51:27,040 --> 00:51:28,040
What debt?

674
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:31,599
Grandpa, you don't have to
hide it from me anymore.

675
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:32,720
I know what's going on.

676
00:51:34,510 --> 00:51:37,800
Don't sweat it.
Leave it to the adults.

677
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:41,680
Grandpa, I'm a grown-up now.
Just tell me.

678
00:51:42,320 --> 00:51:45,960
You think your BL novel
will save this house?

679
00:51:51,170 --> 00:51:52,170
Of course.

680
00:51:53,340 --> 00:51:55,400
I am an award-winning writer,
you know?

681
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:58,560
It's just that
I still can't figure out...

682
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:02,240
what it actually feels like
when a man loves a man.

683
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:05,240
I know I can do it.

684
00:52:29,870 --> 00:52:31,320
You just add them up.

685
00:52:32,900 --> 00:52:34,360
That's how you get these values.

686
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:40,200
We talk.

687
00:52:47,940 --> 00:52:48,940
What do you want?

688
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:51,120
I need to talk to you.

689
00:52:51,400 --> 00:52:53,720
What more do you want from me?
I already backed away.

690
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:03,080
Guy.

691
00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:05,640
How about we give this a try?

692
00:53:15,870 --> 00:53:18,839
What? You're seeing a boy?

693
00:53:18,840 --> 00:53:19,870
Hey, Grandpa.

694
00:53:19,890 --> 00:53:22,090
Don't tell Mom and Dad.

695
00:53:22,730 --> 00:53:24,880
Keep this between us.

696
00:53:25,060 --> 00:53:27,320
When you held hands,
did your heart race?

697
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:30,760
Not at all. More like a jolt.

698
00:53:30,790 --> 00:53:32,200
I can't write this.

699
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:35,399
I just... can't write this...

700
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:41,399
The world keeps
turning every day.

701
00:53:41,400 --> 00:53:46,879
And we keep turning in its play.

702
00:53:46,880 --> 00:53:49,960
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

703
00:53:50,240 --> 00:53:52,720
We just might see
the world within.

704
00:53:52,750 --> 00:53:56,839
Let's walk together, day by day.

705
00:53:56,840 --> 00:54:01,680
Come take the step,
what do you say?

706
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:12,079
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

707
00:54:12,080 --> 00:54:15,839
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

708
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:20,839
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

709
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:23,399
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

710
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:26,079
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

711
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:30,920
And land where
our hearts both grow.

712
00:54:31,240 --> 00:54:37,159
The world keeps
turning every day.

713
00:54:37,160 --> 00:54:42,479
And we keep turning in its play.

714
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:45,720
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

715
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:48,439
We just might see
the world within.

716
00:54:48,440 --> 00:54:52,519
Let's walk together, day by day.

717
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:57,680
Come take the step,
what do you say?
